## Proof of (2.25)

Take some parameters

$$
\theta=(\alpha, \beta, \tau) \in \Theta_{d, \bar{d}} \quad \text { and } \quad \theta_{1}=(\iota, \kappa, \varsigma) \in \Theta_{d, \bar{d}}
$$

Applying (2.9) with

$$
\begin{array}{ll}
m_{1}=(\iota+\kappa m)+\kappa(x-m), & \sigma_{1}=\varsigma \\
m_{2}=(\alpha+\beta m)+\beta(x-m), & \sigma_{2}=\tau
\end{array}
$$

we find that

$$
\begin{aligned}
2 \operatorname{Ent}\left(\delta_{x} K_{\theta_{1}} \mid \delta_{x} K_{\theta}\right)= & \operatorname{Tr}\left(\tau^{-1} \varsigma-I\right)-\log \operatorname{det}\left(\tau^{-1} \varsigma\right) \\
& +\|\tau^{-1 / 2}[((\iota+\kappa m)-(\alpha+\beta m))+(\kappa-\beta)(x-m)]\|_{F}^{2}
\end{aligned}
$$

which implies that

$$
\begin{aligned}
2 \operatorname{Ent}\left(P_{\theta_{1}} \mid P_{\theta}\right)= & 2 \int \nu_{m, \sigma}(d x) \operatorname{Ent}\left(\delta_{x} K_{\theta_{1}} \mid \delta_{x} K_{\theta}\right) \\
= & \operatorname{Tr}\left(\tau^{-1} \varsigma-I\right)-\log \operatorname{det}\left(\tau^{-1} \varsigma\right) \\
& +\left\|\tau^{-1 / 2}((\iota+\kappa m)-(\alpha+\beta m))\right\|_{F}^{2}+\|\tau^{-1 / 2}(\kappa-\beta) \sigma^{1 / 2}\|_{F}^{2}
\end{aligned}
$$

This ends the proof of (2.25).

# F Some technical proofs
## Proof of (2.3)

The symmetric property comes from the fact that

$$
\begin{aligned}
u^{1 / 2}\left(u^{-1 / 2} v u^{-1 / 2}\right)^{1 / 2} u^{1 / 2} & =u^{1 / 2}\left(u^{1 / 2} v^{-1} u^{1 / 2}\right)^{-1 / 2} u^{1 / 2} \\
& =v^{1 / 2}\left(v^{-1 / 2} u v^{-1 / 2}\right)^{1 / 2} v^{1 / 2}
\end{aligned}
$$

and the last assertion comes from the fact that

$$
\left(v^{-1 / 2} u^{1 / 2}\left(u^{1 / 2} v^{-1} u^{1 / 2}\right)^{-1 / 2} u^{1 / 2} v^{-1 / 2}\right)^{2}=v^{-1 / 2} u^{1 / 2} u^{1 / 2} v^{-1 / 2}=v^{-1 / 2} u v^{-1 / 2}
$$
